description:
Jazz bassist Jonah Jonathan interviews Jazz saxophonist Vincent Herring in his home on September 21st 2019. Vincent Herring is one of the most accomplished players of his generation. He has worked with some of the biggest names in music including Nat Adderly, Art Blakey, Horrace Silver, Harold Mabern, Eric Alexander, and many others. He is also an amazing educator and he has been teaching primarily at William Paterson University for many years.
